@7038=~TREETENDER: Although they rarely interact with other gnomes on a daily basis, these nature priests are highly respected for helping to preserve the environment in which their fellows live. Like the druid of humankind, the Treetender takes a fierce interest in his or her domain and will vigorously strive to protect it against all threats. He or she is not a complete recluse, however, and will usually make it to a local village for all the major festivals, as well as helping gnomes (and, sometimes, halflings) who   pass through his or her woods.

Advantages:

- Level 1: Has immunity to Entangle.
- Level 1: Once per day the Treetender can gather herbs and use them to concoct a Potion of Healing. 

HEALING POTION BREWING

Level 1: Creates a Potion of Healing.
Level 10: Creates a Potion of Extra Healing.
Level 20: Creates a Potion of Superior Healing.

- Level 3: Gains immunity to charm.
- Can cast minor spells from the Plant sphere. This includes Entangle (1st), Shillelagh (1st), Barkskin (2nd), Goodberry (2nd), Spike Growth (3rd), Mold Touch (3rd), and Thorn Spray (4th).


Disadvantages:

- They can only become proficient in clubs, quarterstaffs, slings, and any of the weapon styles.
- Cannot cast Animate Dead, Slay Living, or Finger of Death.


Restrictions:

- Must be a gnome.
- Must be a neutral or good alignment~

 @7039=~Through much of your existence you have lived on the outskirts of a gnome village. However, rather than involve yourself in the affairs of your own kind you have instead spent much of your life choosing to make meaningful connections with the forest around you. Curing sickly trees, fighting to stop logging, and even planting your own garden from time to time have all served to keep you interested in and connected with nature.

Still, having read at a young age about the great trees of the north you have long wished to travel there to study them yourself. Unfortunately it has only been until recently that the opportunity to travel to the north has been available. 

As it so happens, a ranger recently established his own dwelling near yours. With your forest in safe hands you pounce on this rare opportunity. After all, your long your time amongst nature has taught you of its own ability to protect itself - and with news of an ally establishing their own dwelling close by you are confident that after your journey you will return to find the forest you have called home to be unscathed. With this in mind you have set out for Icewind Dale, staff in hand.~
