//Breachgnome

@600=~breachgnome~
@601=~Breachgnome~
@602=~BREACHGNOME: The Breachgnome is a heroic defender of gnomekind. They are known to put themselves in harms way, whatever the outcome, and to hold off an enemy as long as is needed. Frequently they receive training from both their own masters as well as members of other races in order to improve their skills at defending from attacks.

Advantages

- Level 1: It can use its Hold the Line ability once per day. It gains an additional use out of this ability every 4 levels.

HOLD THE LINE

When this ability is used the Breachgnome remains still, holding his place in order to defend himself from all attacks made against him. 

When activated the Breachgnome's AC is further reduced by 1 for every 2 levels the Breachgnome has obtained. This is to a maximum of -10 at level 20. The ability lasts for one turn, after which the Breachgnome may move around as needed.

- Level 2: Gains -1 AC every 2 levels, to a maximum of -5 at level 10. 
- Level 3: Becomes immune to Fear

Disadvantages

- Can only gain Grand Mastery in Short Swords, Warhammers, and Axes.
- Can only become specialized in other weapons.
- Can only gain specialization in Sword and Shield Style. No greater than proficiency can be obtained for other weapon styles.

Restrictions

- Must be a gnome
- Must have 16 strength
- Must be a neutral or good alignment~

@603=~Growing up tales of gnomes who held the line while civilians fled were frequently told in your household. Gnomes that would stand against ogres, orcs, and thralls of undead when necessary whenever they could be found. Since your youth you have taken any opportunity available to learn from others of fighting styles, including members of other races, seeking fighting styles that would let you yourself act to defend others in peril.

In time you came to be under the tutelage of a master of the fighting arts. It was through his own advice that you set out for the City of Calimport. There you learned the art of defence from Andar Sciatto, a half-elf Blade of considerable talent. 

It was from him that you learned the art of parrying, a skill that he had clearly mastered. His lessons are lessons you have taken to heart, though you continue to rely on using both a weapon and a shield in combat.

Ultimately however, life in a larger city simply wasn't for you. After a number of months you decided to leave the city and with the knowledge you now possessed you sought to return to your village and settling down, perhaps one day becoming leader of the town watch.

You expected to arrive back to your village with a happy heart, eager to see your master, friends, and family. Instead as you approached the village the signs of an attack became increasingly apparent. Smoke still lingered over parts of the village, while others had been reduced to ash and burnt timber. The signs of gnomes fleeing was also apparent, though how many left alive was not clear.

As you studied the town in search of the origins of the attack it became clear from the direction of the barricades that it had most likely come from a cave in the northern end of the village. At the entrance to this cave lay what you most feared, the lifeless body of your master. He clearly had tried to hold the attack off as long as he could - though it had not been enough. It is clear that without strong, healthy, heroes available the town quickly fell. When you were needed most you were not there, a fact that haunts you to this day.

You left your village and travelled around, hoping to hear of survivors. Unfortunately, tracking the remainder of your kind proved difficult. Most of the humanoids you spoke to shared any interest in sharing what (if anything) they knew.

Having found no trace of what was left of your village your sights turned towards other areas of the realms that could use your aid. Hearing frequent tales of orc, bugbear, and goblin raids in the north convinced you that your help is needed there. You have since decided to leave all that you know hoping to serve as a stalwart defender of the villages of the Ten Towns. You have set your sights on Easthaven, a small fishing village near the Spine of the World, hoping to render whatever assistance you can for it.~
@604=~A gnome that fights to hold the line to let others escape.~

@605=~Hold the Line~
