@667=~You grew up in a small village surrounded by large cliffs, rivers, and waterfalls. Yet, despite growing up in this tranquil setting, you always found more comfort in a book than what lay outside your door.

Though your parents had some degree of income and could afford to nurture your book reading habits they soon realized that there was a more appropriate setting for you to live. They arranged to have a nearby monastery of Oghma take care of you. The clerics and monks of Oghma there have since became second parents to you, particularly as you have grown older and became more aware. You still keep in contact with your parents, though these days that has become more difficult as you are often sent on tasks to various libraries across Faerun. 

Having returned from a recent excursion to the library in Candlekeep you found yourself approached immediately by Loremaster Janos. He described the pressing need for you to speak with the head of the monastery, as it had been decided that you were needed on yet another mission.

The head of your monastery described to you where you would be going. An icy region of the north called Icewind Dale. It was the strong belief in the older members of your order that there was significant lost knowledge and books to be found there. 

You set out for Icewind Dale, walking staff in hand, with what few supplies will be needed for your long journey.~
