@695=~Your time as a Disciple in the Disciples of the White Rod has taught you if nothing else the effectiveness and value of pain. Even though you are only an initiate in your order you have watched powerful political figures begging at your masters feet, hoping to be spared the inevitable pain they were about the experience.

Loviatar teaches that the world is full of pain and torment, and the best one can do is to suffer those blows that cannot be avoided and deal as much pain back to those who offend. It is with this goal in mind that all Disciples of the White Rod train under.

Called by your master to meet with the head of your order, you have been summoned to spread fear of your order to other areas of the realms. While others in your order prefer warmer climates you have always taken a personal affinity for the cold and the pain it can inflict. You now travel to a region in the  northwest of Faerun called Icewind Dale. If nothing else while there you hope to test your own abilities against whatever awaits you in that inhospitable land.~
