@703=~As a member of the Disciples of the Yielding Way you have frequently served as a protector for Eldath's clergy. Sometimes this has involved efforts to settle disputes between warring parties, while other times it has involved protecting those looking to find isolated groves and fastnesses.

Thankfully so far as has been well. Occasionally you have sparred with others of your faith. However, you lack true battlefield experience. Your order firmly believes in avoiding provoking violence, going so far as to never hit first in battle, and you personally find more interest in the cataloging of plants and animals than combat. 

Though you have so far only served as an initiate in your order it was always your hope that one day you would be granted the chance to prove yourself ready for greater responsibilities.

That time came soon enough, as it was only recently that you were summoned by your master. The head of your order had instructed him to send you, and you alone, to the icy region of Icewind Dale. There you are tasked to assess the situation in the north and do what you can to honour Eldath's ways. Eldath's teachings will be a stranger in these lands, but it is the belief of your master that some good can come from your visit. With that in mind you travel to the tiny fishing village of Easthaven. There you hope to find a guide to help you traverse the terrain as you visit the settlements that make up the Ten Towns.~
@704=~A monk who follows Eldath~



@705=~monk of the old order~
@706=~Monk of the Old Order~
@707=~MONK OF THE OLD ORDER: Monks of the Old Order do not worship any deity, but are devoted to the philosophy espoused by a deity who is either now dead or has never existed on the Material Plane of Toril. The monks contradict themselves on this point, but the deity's identity isn't important to them, it's the message they care about. The Old Order never has huge monasteries, but has spread widely throughout Faerun.


