@708=~You have spent much of your life acting as a servant in an otherwise rarely heard of order of monks called The Old Order. Through them you have learned of a deity of great wisdom and clarity, and as you have grown older your faith towards this nameless presence has only hardened.

Members of your order are always interested in spreading your faith's philosophy to all those who will listen. Your order however has had difficulty recruiting new members and with that in mind it has begun sending monks of the order to the most remote regions of the world looking to gather new recruits.

You have been tasked with traveling to Icewind Dale. The many towns and villages are likely in need of more faith, and you are more than happy to oblige.~
@709=~A monk that seems to worship a god who nobody knows~




@710=~monk of the order of the long death~
@711=~Monk of the Order of the Long Death~
@712=~MONK OF THE ORDER OF THE LONG DEATH: These monks seek for the secrets of life by studying death. It is the condition of being dead that concerns them most, and not what lies beyond. Obtaining the perfect death, whatever form that happens to be, is something that they revere. Their laboratories are full of decaying, dying, and dead animal and plant specimens that they study with detached interest. They frequently purchase rare specimens that they cannot obtain easily themselves from adventurers and merchants and rarely adventure themselves.


Advantages:

