@713=~"Death is but a vessel to carry us to salvation."

This was the final lesson you were taught by the hands of your former master. Truly they were words of wisdom, and had his death not been at your own hands you might have cared to heed them.

As a member of the Order of the Long death you seek to cause a painful death for anyone you encounter, whenever possible. Death is not something to be feared so much as it is something that deserves to be perfected.

Most monks in your order come and go as they please, spreading fear amongst locals of your place of worship in the process. Stories of loved ones dying violently in their sleep have long since plagued local villagers, such that your own temple can come under siege repeatedly in recent years.

Recognizing the possibility of relocating to somewhere more remote the elders of your temple have suggested the possibility of the north as a new home. Cold and death are frequent bedfellows of the population there and the occasional dead villager or two should not arouse the same level of suspicion it does in the south.

It has been requested that you travel to Icewind Dale, a remote region in the north, to investigate possible sites of relocation. The possibility of adventure and the chance to prove yourself made you accept this challenge. You have set off for the small fishing village of Easthaven, a remote village and one that seems might suit your unique needs.~
