@720=~Until recently you lived a rather solemn existence working in a monastery atop the Nether Mountains. Travelers to your temple were rare, as few dared risk facing the bands of orcs that frequently roam the area.

As an initiate in your temple you are often asked to scout the land and to keep apprised of orc numbers.
The orcs themselves now showed little interest in the residents of your temple, having long ago learned of the power its defenders possessed, but caution still was warranted.

It was during a recent patrol on your part that you came upon the corpse of a traveller. The orc arrows piercing his gut made the cause of his death clear enough, but what was more interesting was the contents of his pack.

Inside you find maps and books regarding Icewind Dale, a region of the north far to the north-west of your temple. The markings on the map intrigued you, as they seemed to suggest this traveller was travelling to the tiny inlet of Easthaven, but the reasons for his traveling were not immediately apparent.

As you began to study these books it became clear that the reason for this traveller taking such a dangerous path was that he was seeking adventurers and allies willing to explore the region with him. For reasons that remain unclear he had decided that your temple was a possible source of allies, an opinion that cost him dearly. 

Still, you took your discoveries to the head of your temple. There while standing before the head of your order you were told that this could be an opportunity to expand the temples reach. For too long you have been isolationists, leaving yourselves removed from events across Faerun. With more clear evidence of events transpiring in the north year old rumours of followers of Grumbar showing interest in the north now seem to concern the head of your order greatly. They have tasked you with traveling to Icewind Dale to see what is unfolding yourself. You left shortly thereafter, taking only the minimal supplies needed for such a long journey.~
